The  World Bank  will give  Burkina
Faso  $115 million for agricultural projects in the around the
Bagre hydroelectricity dam, said Issa Djibrila, the head of
the project at the lender.  Burkina Faso â€™s government will use the money to invest in
farming, livestock and fish farming in the waters around the
dam, 240 kilometers (149 miles) from the capital, Ouagadougou,
